President Obama and Vice President Biden will hold a White House Recovery and Reinvestment Act Implementation Conference on March 12th, 2009. The conference aims to ensure that the funds invested and spent as part of the Recovery Act are effective, transparent, and efficient. Each state's Governor has been invited to send their senior official working on Recovery Act implementation to learn about available programs and initiatives. The conference will provide an opportunity for state officials to share ideas and best practices, as well as hear presentations from Cabinet Secretaries and Administration officials. Vice President Biden, who is overseeing the implementation of the Recovery Act, emphasized the importance of states partnering with the federal government to spend the funds wisely and with transparency. President Obama will attend the conference briefly, while Vice President Biden will address the conference. The remarks from both leaders will be shared with the press.